author: Mike Okay
description:
Once, the Aral Sea was one of the largest lakes on Earth. Today, it’s a dried-up desert filled with abandoned Soviet shipwrecks, rusting on sand where waves used to hit. In this video, I travel to the Aral Sea region to see what’s left, meet people who still live here, and spend the night inside a Soviet shipwreck that hasn’t touched water in decades.
